The paper deals with complexity and tractability of computational problems, specifically Holant problems, which are typically studied in the computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also involves graph theory (cs.DM), combinatorial optimization (cs.GT), and computational geometry (cs.CG) in its analysis and proofs.
